{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Grease a dish (18 x 6 cm) and set aside (see Tip).","Place butter into mixing bowl and melt <b>1 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside. Do not clean mixing bowl.","Place 300 g of the water, 70 g of the sugar and 30 g of the cocoa into mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>, then cook <b>3 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>. Transfer sauce into a jug and set aside. Do not clean mixing bowl.","Place flour, baking powder, salt, eggs, milk, vanilla, remaining 30 g cocoa, remaining 70 g sugar and reserved melted butter into mixing bowl and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add chocolate and combine <b>5 sec\/\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides and base of mixing bowl with spatula to ensure mixture is completely combined. Transfer batter into prepared dish. Gently pour reserved sauce over batter. Cover with a piece of baking paper and seal with a piece of aluminium foil. Clean mixing bowl.","Place remaining 1000 g water into mixing bowl. Place Varoma dish into position, lay 2 wooden skewers (18-19 cm) across base of Varoma dish and carefully place baking dish on top. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>45-50 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b> or until centre of pudding is cooked. Remove Varoma and set aside. Discard steaming water.","Place reserved cherry juice, arrowroot and Kirsch (optional) into mixing bowl and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>, then cook <b>5 min\/100°C\/speed 3<b>, <strong>without measuring cup.<\/strong> Place cherries into a bowl and pour sauce over cherries.","Serve pudding warm with cherry sauce and double cream."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["60 g unsalted butter, cut into pieces, plus extra for greasing","1300 g water","140 g soft dark brown sugar","60 g cocoa powder","180 g plain flour","2 tsp baking powder","1 pinch salt","2 eggs","130 g full cream milk","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","40 g dark chocolate melts","400 g canned cherries, drained and juice reserved","2 tsp arrowroot starch","60 g Kirsch (optional)","double cream, to serve"]}],"id":"r145112","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-drAKrsB0hCk\/XZWdx2x-qNI\/AAAAAAAAeqI\/pE9V3zSbtaI_lnQnRZkmNI5uqQbvLFdUgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_MKsvG6JzPHOzNuDs.png","title":"Black forest pudding","publishedAt":"2017-07-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"9.5 g","fat":"26.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"63.4 g","calories":"2220 kJ \/ 528 kcal"},"usefulItems":"round ceramic dish (18 x 6 cm), bowl, jug, baking paper, aluminium foil, wooden skewers","hintsAndTricks":["As long as your Varoma lid will fit securely in place, you can steam pudding in an oval ceramic dish (19-24 x 7 cm)."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 15m","6 portions"]}